Every poetry expert we talked to pointed to the way poetry is taught in schools as the biggest barrier to entry for most people.
But even she says, "people don't trust themselves because they're thinking in the back of their minds 'no, there's a right answer, there's a correct answer and I wanna be sure I'm not giving a wrong answer.'"
It helps them find the groove of their writing, which is essentially what you're trying to do with someone else's poetry.
Or better yet, when you can, head to your local poetry reading.
